The paper deals with the problem of transmitting a sequence of messages over a packet erasure channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a construction of optimal streaming codes, which involves coding theory (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper considers a specific channel loss model and characterizes the maximum achievable rate, which is a problem in cryptography (cs.CR).
